Fair enough that openssl might not be the way to go here.

What mostly worries me is that there is no error handling whatsoever if the string doesn't match what we're expecting, or fails to parse, or has unacceptable characters in it.  I also am not a big fan of adding yet another boost dependency (boost tokenizer) when the parser we're trying to write can be easily done with a single while loop, while at the same time avoiding a bunch of the string copies that seem to have been made.



I took a little time to doctor up the (untested) version of what I'd like to see instead, which has no string copies (with the exception of copying it into the output) and doesn't have any dependencies on boost.

static void updateCertIssuerOrSubject(const std::string &s,
                                      nlohmann::json &j)
{
    const std::string_view::iterator i = s.begin();
    while (i != s.end())
    {
        const std::string_view::iterator tokenBegin = i;
        /* Collect the type */
        while (i != s.end() && *i != '='){
            i++;
        }
        if (i == s.end())
        {
            BMCWEB_LOG_ERROR("Hit end of string before finding the '='");
            return;
        }
        const std::string_view key = s.substr(tokenBegin, i);
        i++;
        tokenBegin = i;
        while (i != s.end() && *i != ','){
            i++;
        }
        const std::string_view value = s.substr(tokenBegin, i);

        if (key == "L")
        {
            value["City"] = value;
        }
        else if (key == "CN")
        {
            value["CommonName"] = value;
        }
        else if (key == "C")
        {
            value["Country"] = value;
        }
        else if (key == "O")
        {
            value["Organization"] = value;
        }
        else if (key == "OU")
        {
            value["OrganizationalUnit"] = value;
        }
        else if (key == "ST")
        {
            value["State"] = value;
        }

        while (i != s.end() && *i != ' '){
            i++;
        }
    }
}

